data.event: Much of what is now Kendall was purchased from the State of Florida in 1883 by the Florida Land and Mortgage Company.

event.title: moved to the area in the 1900s

data.event: It was named for Henry John Broughton Kendall, a director of Florida Land and Mortgage who moved to the area in the 1900s to manage the company's land.
A post office opened in 1914, and the first school opened in 1929.
